U.S. Report on Human Rights and Democracy under Fire 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 5 (KCNA) -- Some days ago, the U.S. State Department slandered the DPRK again in its "2004-2005 report on U.S. efforts for human rights and democracy."
 In this regard, Rodong Sinmun Tuesday in a signed commentary says: 
 The U.S. dared talk this or that about issues of "human rights" and "democracy" in the DPRK, falsifying truth. This is an unbearable insult to the Korean people, an outrageous interference in their internal affairs and a blatant challenge to justice. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. is the most repressive society in the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Citing concrete facts to prove that the U.S. has mercilessly cracked down upon and arrested all forms of socio-political activities of the people by fascistizing its ruling system and inhumanely abused and punished prisoners in various parts of the world, the commentary goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. is a crude violator of human rights and a strangler of freedom and democracy. The ulterior aim sought by the U.S. in vociferating about the "improvement of human rights and democracy" is to realize its ambition for world domination and its immediate purpose is to bring down the anti-U.S. independent countries. In a word, the U.S. seeks to tarnish the image of the above-said countries and isolate them internationally under the pretexts of the issues of "human rights" and "democracy" and instigate the counterrevolutionary elements to stoke the social confusion and discontent in a bid to force those countries to change their regimes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The spearhead of its operation is directed to the DPRK. Much upset by the might of the DPRK, the Bush forces even adopted the "North Korean Human Rights Act" aimed at "overturning its regime" in a bid to escalate their criminal human rights offensive against the DPRK &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. should abandon its shameless sinister intention to overthrow the anti-U.S. independent countries and achieve its ambition for world domination under the signboard of the "improvement of human rights and democracy."

Sports Games for Mangyongdae Cup Opens 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 5 (KCNA) -- Sports Games for Mangyongdae Cup opened on the occasion of the birth anniversary of President Kim Il Sung (April 15), the greatest jubilee of the nation.
 This annual event marks an important occasion in developing the sports technique of the country as it is a sports festival bringing together at least 8,000 ace athletes from more than 100 sports groups in Pyongyang and local areas. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants will compete in at least 30 events including football, basketball, volleyball, boxing, judo, swimming, shooting and ice hockey to be held in Pyongyang, Sariwon, Nampho, Wonsan and other areas of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 An opening ceremony was held at the Volleyball Gymnasium in Chongchun Street, Pyongyang on Monday. At the ceremony Mun Jae Dok, chairman of the Physical Culture and Sports Guidance Commission, made an opening speech to be followed by speeches. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there was Kim Jung Rin, secretary of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea.

Japan Should Never Be Allowed to Sit on UNSC 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 5 (KCNA) -- Japan is now becoming desperate in its bid for permanent membership of the UN Security Council. This fully betrays its
shameless and cunning moves to emerge a political power and realize its dream for overseas expansion by taking advantage of this position.
 Minju Joson Tuesday says this in a signed commentary. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Referring to the fact that the Japanese Foreign Ministry recently worked out a "diplomatic blue book" which clarifies that the main target of Japan's diplomacy this year is to "get permanent membership of the UNSC and make international contributions commensurate with its status, the commentary goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan has no elementary qualification to be even a member nation of the UN, much less becoming a UNSC permanent member. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The past history of Japan is recorded with bloody wars of aggression fought against humankind. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan is now working hard to repeat the above-said history, zealously whitewashing and beautifying it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan should not be allowed to make a pitch for permanent membership of the UNSC in view of the international community's cool reaction to it and in the light of the purpose of the UN reform. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The world should select only those responsible countries which have made great contributions to defending global peace and security and can do so in future as permanent members of the UNSC. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 But if permanent membership is given to such countries which persistently commit crimes against humanity in pursuit of selfish interests as Japan, it will not lead the UN to reform but to a collapse and herald its doom. This will be as clear as daylight. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the countries should ponder over the political upheaval and grave consequences to be entailed by Japan's pitch for UNSC permanent membership. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan's dream for this would never come true unless it totally redresses its crime-woven past history and starts with a clean slate.

Mongolian Crewmen's Celebration Meeting Held 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Hungnam, April 4 (KCNA) -- A meeting of crewmen of Mongolian-flagged ship Smooth Voyager was held at Hungnam Port in the East Sea of Korea on Monday to celebrate the 12th anniversary of leader Kim Jong Il's election as chairman of the National Defence Commission of the DPRK.
 Speakers at the meeting said that his election as chairman of the NDC of the DPRK marked a historic event not only for the Korean people but for the progressive humankind aspiring after independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people have worked fresh miracles in firmly defending the sovereignty of the country, the dignity of the nation and socialism and in building a great prosperous powerful nation under the guidance of Kim Jong Il, they noted, adding that victory and glory are always in store for the heroic Korean people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A congratulatory letter to Kim Jong Il was adopted at the meeting.

Russian Presidential Orchestra Performs before Full House 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 5 (KCNA) -- The Presidential Orchestra of the Russian Federation gave a performance at the People's Palace of Culture here Monday
before full house.
 It was appreciated by officials concerned, servicepersons and staff members of the Russian embassy here. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performers enthusiastically sang Korean songs including "Song Devoted to Comrade Kim Jong Il" to deeply impress the audience. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The orchestra of Korean song "Mungyong Pass" made the audience recollect with deep emotion the heroic feats fighters of the Korean People's Army performed by unhesitatingly dedicating their lives to the struggle for their beloved country, true to the leadership of President Kim Il Sung during the last Fatherland Liberation War. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 People's Artiste Lyudmila Nikolaeva presented Korean song "I Know It Now" in fluent Korean. The song mesmerized the audience as it reflects the intense loyalty of the army and people of the DPRK to the leader and their ardent patriotism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In their numbers including female vocal solo "Oriole", male vocal solo "Oh, My Love" and "Dance of Polovets" from chorus opera "Grand Prince Igori" the performers truthfully represented the optimistic life and national emotion of the Russian people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the chorus "Just War" conducted by Merited Artiste and Prof. Lev Kontorovich Russian artistes successfully depicted the indomitable fighting spirit of the servicepersons and people of Russia who valiantly fought to defend the country from the aggressors. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performance ended with the chorus of Russian song "My Country". It was acclaimed by the audience for its high ideological value and artistry.

International Art Festival to Open Soon
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 5 (KCNA) -- The 23rd April Spring Friendship Art Festival will be held in Pyongyang on the occasion of the Day of the Sun.
 This festival will attract world famous art troupes and artistes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Among them are the ensemble of the Moscow Tchaikovsky State Conservatory with a long tradition, the State Academy Chorus Named after Sveshnikov and the Russian Kazakh Dance Troupe. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The festival will also be participated in by singers and dancers of the Hangchou Dance Troupe of China who won national concours or were high appreciated at domestic art festivals and competitions several times. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Among the participants will be a Polish song and dance troupe well known to the Korean people through its several performance tour of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Pyongyang will welcome international and national concours winners, people's artistes and merited artistes and famous artistes from Ukraine, Japan, UK, Greece, France and other countries who will bring with them the repertoires prepared with sincerity.

Birth Anniversary of Revolutionary Fighter Cha Kwang Su Marked
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 5 (KCNA) -- The centennial birth anniversary of Cha Kwang Su, an anti-Japanese revolutionary fighter, has been marked in the DPRK.
 A national meeting took place at the People's Palace of Culture here Tuesday to commemorate the anniversary.
 Present there were senior Party, state and army officials. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Vice Marshal of the Korean People's Army Kim Il Chol, member of the DPRK National Defence Commission and minister of the People's Armed Forces, made a report at the meeting. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 According to the report, Cha Kwang Su came of a poor peasant family in Ryongchon County, North Phyongan Province on April 5, 1905. He had gone through the bitter sorrow and suffering of a ruined nation from his childhood, being subject to the severe oppression of the Japanese imperialist aggressors. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He had wandered about at home and abroad, not knowing what to do before he found his leader who would indicate the right way for struggle. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was only under the exceptional leadership of President Kim Il Sung who was hewing out the path of the Korean revolution that Cha found himself worth living as a true revolutionary and turned over a new leaf in his life. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He became a member of the Down-with-Imperialism Union, a genuine revolutionary organization of Juche type formed by the President, and later a leading member of the Anti-Imperialist Youth League and the Young Communist League of Korea. And he made all his efforts for the foundation of the Korean Revolutionary Army and the Anti-Japanese People's Guerrilla Army (AJPGA) while working hard to expand the basic party organizations as a core member of the Society for Rallying Comrades which was the first party organization. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After the birth of the AJPGA, Cha assumed an important post of its chief of staff and assisted with heart and soul the President in his revolutionary activities for the strengthening and development of the anti-Japanese armed struggle, thus greatly contributing to pioneering the revolutionary cause of Juche and ensuring its victorious advance. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He died a heroic death at a bloody battle site in Dunhua on Oct. 30, Juche 21 (1932). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reporter noted that he had upheld the leader of the revolution with the purest conscience and the highest sense of obligation and devoted his sincere heart of loyalty to realizing the idea and cause of the leader. His noble life was that of an ardent loyal subject who made distinguished contributions to the history of the movement of the Korean revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  The heroic events in the first period of the Korean revolution--the formation of the Korean Revolutionary Army, the laying of mass foundation for the anti-Japanese armed struggle, the struggle for acquiring weapons, the foundation of the AJPGA and the start of the anti-Japanese war--were associated with the precious feats of Cha, who devoted his all to materializing the President's idea and line of giving priority to arms, upholding them as the only banner of righteous struggle of the Korean revolution, the reporter said. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  He emphasized: Cha's life is a brilliant model teaching us how a revolutionary should hold his leader in esteem and live and fight for the country and the people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  On the occasion of his centennial birth anniversary, wreaths were placed before his bust at the Revolutionary Martyrs Cemetery in Mt. Taesong here today. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Meanwhile, Pyongyang-based newspapers Tuesday carry articles telling about his undying revolutionary feats.

"Complete Collection of Kim Il Sung's Works" Published&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 5 (KCNA) -- A "Complete Collection of Kim Il Sung's Works" Vol.58 was published by the Workers' Party of Korea Publishing House. The complete collection is a library of the immortal Juche idea which carries President Kim Il Sung's famous works systematically and comprehensively in chronological order.
 Contained in the book are 30 works such as reports, speeches and talks made by the President from October Juche 64 (1975) to March Juche 65(1976).
 In the work "On the Occasion of the 30th Anniversary of the Foundation of the Workers' Party of Korea", he reviewed the signal achievements and feats the WPK made for independence and building of socialism during the last 30 years. And he clarified the ideas, theories and policies to further strengthen the Party and enhance its leading role in order to expedite the revolution and construction. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Among those works are "On Putting the Production of Iron and Steel on a Normal Basis" and "On Effectively Ensuring Labor Assistance to the Countryside and the Guidance over Farming" in which tasks and ways are laid down to bring a fresh surge in the socialist economic construction. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There are also "On the Need for Chongryon to Successfully Carry Out the Work for National Reunification", "On the Need for Chongryon Scientists to Establish Juche in Scientific Researches" and other works, which advance tasks facing the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongryon) and the Koreans in Japan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Besides, the book carries "The Non-Aligned Movement Is a Mighty Anti-Imperialist Revolutionary Force of Our Times", "Talk with the Editor-in-Chief of the Japanese Newspaper Mainichi Shimbun and His Party" and other works, in which the President made clear the significance and role of the non-aligned movement in the development of the world revolution and international life and clarified the principled issues in accelerating the movement.

Message of Condolences to Department of State of Vatican
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 5 (KCNA) -- Samuel Jang Jae On, chairman of the Central Committee of the Korean Catholics Association, Tuesday sent a message of
condolences to the Department of State of the Vatican over the demise of Pope John Paul II.
 The message says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Upon hearing the sudden sad news that His Holiness Pope John Paul II passed away, I express deep condolences. 
 All the Catholic believers of our country are also offering memorial service in deep grief at the Jangchung Cathedral in Pyongyang and family warship places across the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The feats of His Holiness John Paul II, who devoted himself to the development of the Catholic faith community as the proxy for Jesus Christ on earth and the supreme minister of Church, will remain long together with the history of the Catholic Church amid the blessings of the Lord. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 I pray for his eternal happiness from above.

"Chonggokkinaje" Made in DPRK
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 5 (KCNA) -- "I could have not moved even an inch since my cerebral thrombosis a few years ago. To my astonishment, however, I could move a week after I started to take Chonggokkinaje and walk a month later.
Since then, I have frequently gone to hospital for medical check-up. But doctors have said that my blood is clean." This is what Pak Kun Sik, 69, residing in Mangyongdae District, Pyongyang, said. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Chonggokkinaje, thrombolysis element of which is of 10,000 International Unit, was developed by the Microbial Enzyme Research Institute of the Life Science Faculty of Kim Il Sung University. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Chief Ri Hyon Gwang of the institute told KCNA that more than 90 percent of cerebral thrombosis patients have recovered their health thanks to the Chonggokkinaje. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Chonggokkinaje, which directly dissolves fibrin, a main cause of thrombus, has a strong capacity to dissolve micro thrombi in blood. The medicine is potent for thrombus-causing diseases including cerebral thrombosis and myocardial infarction. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is also efficacious for arteriosclerosis and hyperlipemia as it dissolves elastin and neutral fat. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Chonggokkinaje protects such main proteins as hemoglobin and albumin from radical peroxide and stress oxide. It, therefore, prevents and cures toxicosis by stress and reduces re-formation of thrombus. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 One can take it without doctor's prescription as it has no side-effects. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is effective for eight hours after dosage. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It enjoys great popularity at local and foreign markets. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
