New Stone Production Method Invented
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 5 (KCNA) -- A new method of stone production has been invented by scientists of Kim Chaek University of Technology in the Democratic People's Republic of Korea.
 The method, based on a newly manufactured stonecutting machine, makes it possible to produce quantities of quality stones and thus to meet the ever growing demand for quality building stones. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Associate Prof. Jong Il Chol, who had led the research team, told KCNA that the new method is economically effective more than drilling and blasting and other methods. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The stones excavated by the method are like crudely grinded ones and have not cracks. Its actual extraction rate is over 95 percent and productivity is 20 times that of previous methods. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As it cuts stone mountains in order, it produces no muck and keeps quarries clean.
